In Static Methods you dont have to create a an instance of a class to use the methods. If a method with the [b]static[/b] keyword, the method can be called without first creating an instance of the class, this is becasue static methods are called from classes, not from objects.

The [b]main[/b] method of a java app must be declared with the [b]static[/b] keyword, this is how we know....
That's becasue when you start a java program by using the java command from cmd, java doesnt create an instance of the application class, instead it bascially makes it the [b]static main method[/b].

Many Java Programs are made up of static methods, however this tutorial is only for you guys to understan them better, most realistic programs require that you create one or more objects that the program uses to exacute.

I hope the guide has helped you understand the basics of static methods, and how you use them.

